  "response": "The frequency with which people buy new smartphones can vary widely based on personal preferences, financial situations, and technological needs. On average, many consumers tend to upgrade their phones every two to three years. This timing often aligns with the typical length of carrier contracts or installment plans. However, some individuals may choose to upgrade more frequently to keep up with the latest technology, while others might keep their phones for longer if they are still functioning well and meeting their needs.",
